<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4358.2.6>
    dc:creator "Jałoszyński, Paweł" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomy of ' Euconnus complex'. Part XVI. Alloconophron Franz transferred to Anhoraeomorphus Franz as subgenus, with notes on systematic position of Noctophus Casey (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Scydmaeninae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1068388> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1068388>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–16. Morphological structures of Euconnus (Noctophus) schmitti (Casey). Dorsal habitus of holotype female (14); head, prothorax and elytral base in dorsal view (15); head, prothorax and anterior portion of pterothorax in ventral view (16). Abbreviations: abp, antebasal pit; bef, basal elytral fovea; bst, basisternal part of prosternum; hr, hypostomal ridge; hyr, hypomeral ridge; ptp, posterior tentorial pit; nss, notosternal suture; smn, submentum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1068388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

